ater\n- `designs/issue-43/mockup.html` - High-fidelity mockup (954 lines)\n- `de
signs/issue-43/wireframe.svg` - Wireframe (243 lines)\n\n**Blocking Issues**: No
ne - this is a design PR, no code that could break functionality.\n\n**Major Iss
ues**:\n1. **Missing Maestro `identifier` in Accessibility spec**: The design-sp
ec\'s Accessibility section (8.2) only specifies `label` and `tooltip` for Seman
tics, but completely omits `identifier`. Per `docs/design-docs/flutter.md` lines
251-258, `identifier` is essential for Maestro E2E (`tapOn: { id: "xxx" }`). Sin
ce matching is a core user journey that MUST have E2E coverage per `docs/design-
docs/issue-workflow.md` lines 75-79 and 83-86, this omission means the downstrea
m implementation Agent won\'t know to add identifiers, causing E2E tests to fail
.\n\n2. **Missing `onTapDown` requirement for Maestro compatibility**: The inter
action spec (5.1) describes swipe gestures and button clicks but doesn\'t mandat
e `onTapDown` instead of `onTap`. Per `flutter.md` lines 295-314, Maestro\'s `AC
TION_CLICK` only generates DOWN+UP without gesture trajectory, so `onTap` won\'t
fire. This is critical for the Pass/Like buttons and other tappable elements.\n\
n3. **PR doesn\'t update stale cross-references**: `prd/v1-matching.md` referenc
es `designs/issue-4/`, and `docs/api/matching.md` also references `designs/issue
-4/design-spec.md`. This PR (issue-43) should update these references to point t
o issue-43 assets, but it doesn\'t. The `docs-to-update.txt` acknowledges `prd/v
1-matching.md` needs updating, but the PR diff doesn\'t include it.\n\n**Minor I
ssues**:\n1. **Design spec location deviates from template**: `TEMPLATE-design.m
d` specifies design specs should go in `docs/design-docs/ui-specs/<feature>/spec
.md` and wireframes in `docs/design-docs/ui-specs/<feature>/wireframes/`. This P
R places them in `designs/issue-43/`. While `designs/issue-XXX/` is also mention
ed for visual assets, the spec doc location is inconsistent with existing patter
ns (`docs/design-docs/ui-specs/auth/`, `dev-tools/`, `profile/`).\n\n2. **Missin
g E2E flow design for Matching**: Given that matching is a core user journey, th
e design should identify which Maestro E2E flows need to be created. Per `issue-
workflow.md` lines 83-86, new user flows MUST have `.maestro/flows/<flow>.yaml`.
The design spec doesn\'t mention E2E flows at all.\n\n3. **EmptyMatchListView pa
th inconsistency with docs/modules/matching.md**: The design spec puts `EmptyMat
chListView` in `apps/mobile/lib/presentation/widgets/empty_match_list_view.dart`
, but `docs/modules/matching.md` doesn\'t list it in the page-level Widget secti
on (only `EmptyRecommendationView` is there). The design spec should be consiste
nt with the module doc, or the module doc should be updated.\n\n**Positive obser
vations**:\n- Design tokens mostly align with existing `tokens.md`\n- Component 
hierarchy (atom/molecule/organism) is correct\n- Widgetbook use-case requirement
s are specified\n- States (loading, empty, error, match success) are well-define
d\n- Touch target sizes are specified correctly\n- Color contrast requirements a
re mentioned\n- Responsive adaptation is documented\n- The design doesn\'t intro
duce hardcoded colors against project rules\n\n**Verification Results**:\n- Full
