n spec location inconsistent with template\n\n**Conclusion**: NEEDS_MAJOR_FIX - 
The missing Maestro accessibility identifiers and onTapDown requirements are maj
or because they will cause downstream implementation to produce E2E-untestable c
ode, violating project standards.\n\nWait, let me reconsider the severity. The P
R is design-only. The issues I found are design specification gaps. Should they 
be Blocking? \n\n- Missing `identifier` in design spec: This will cause the impl
ementation to miss Maestro identifiers. But is it Blocking? The implementation a
gent could still add them if they read flutter.md. But the design spec is suppos
ed to be the authoritative source for this feature\'s design. If it doesn\'t spe
cify them, there\'s a high risk they\'ll be missed.\n\nActually, looking more ca
refully at `flutter.md`, the Semantics section is a general coding requirement, 
not something every design spec needs to re-state. However, the design spec DOES
have an Accessibility section (8.2) that lists Semantics properties - it just om
